</FONT><B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=4><P>Initial Steps in Solving Linear Equations</P></B></FONT>
<FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=2>
<P>The basics of solving a linear equation are described in Lesson 18. Work through 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 a~?">section a</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 b 0~?">section b</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 c 0~?">section c</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 d 0~?">section d</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 e 0~?">section e</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 f~?">section f</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 g~?">section g</a>, 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 h 0~?">section h</a>, and 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 18 i 0~?">section i</a>. Solving a linear equation is also illustrated on page 1 of your lecture notes.</P>  

<P>Now try <a href="launch.htm#q0607">q0607</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0369">q0369</a>.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
</FONT><B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=4><P>Further Linear Equations</P></B></FONT>
<FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=2>
<P>Some linear equations can be more difficult to solve because they involve fractions or perhaps brackets.<P>

<P>If fractions appear in an equation we normally eliminate them first and then solve the equation. To eliminate the fractions we multiply each side of the equation by the Lowest Common Multiple (LCM) of 
the denominators. Work through Lesson 1-3, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 3 a~?">section a</a>, and 
<a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 3 c 0~?">section c</a> for a revision of the factors of a number and the LCM of two or more numbers. 
Then study Lesson 1-23 <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 23 a 0~?">section a</a>, which describes in detail how to solve a fractional equation.</P>

<P>Also work with equations which include brackets or letters
in Lesson 1-23 <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 23 b 0~?">section b</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 23 c 0~?">section c</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 23 d 0~?">section d</a>.  
Now try question <a href="launch.htm#q0034">q0034</a>.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>This is the <B>end</B> of the Revision Plan on Linear Equations.</P>
